Here are Java programs to address your questions:

**1. Simple String Program to Take Input from User:**
```java
import java.util.Scanner;

public class InputStringExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Enter a string: ");
        String inputString = scanner.nextLine();
        System.out.println("You entered: " + inputString);
        scanner.close();
    }
}
```

**2. How to Concatenate Two Strings in Java?**
```java
public class StringConcatenationExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str1 = "Hello";
        String str2 = "World";
        String result = str1 + " " + str2;
        System.out.println("Concatenated String: " + result);
    }
}
```

**3. How to Find the Length of a String in Java?**
```java
public class StringLengthExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String text = "Hello, World!";
        int length = text.length();
        System.out.println("Length of the string: " + length);
    }
}
```

**4. How to Compare Two Strings in Java?**
```java
public class StringComparisonExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str1 = "Hello";
        String str2 = "Hello";
        
        // Using equals method for comparison
        boolean areEqual = str1.equals(str2);
        
        System.out.println("Are the strings equal? " + areEqual);
    }
}
```

**5. Program to Find the Length of the String "refrigerator":**
```java
public class StringLengthExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String text = "refrigerator";
        int length = text.length();
        System.out.println("Length of the string: " + length);
    }
}
```

**6. Program to Check If the Letter 'e' Is Present in the Word 'Umbrella':**
```java
public class LetterPresenceExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String word = "Umbrella";
        boolean hasE = word.contains("e");
        System.out.println("Does the word contain 'e'? " + hasE);
    }
}
```

**7. Program to Delete All Consonants from the String "Hello, Have a Good Day":**
```java
public class RemoveConsonantsExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String text = "Hello, have a good day";
        String result = text.replaceAll("[^aeiouAEIOU ]", "");
        System.out.println("String after removing consonants: " + result);
    }
}
```

These programs demonstrate various string operations, including input, concatenation, length, comparison, and manipulation.